SUMMARY: Easter EGGSTRAVAGANZA!
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a fun-filled EGGSTRAVAGANZA across The Distillery
  Historic District!\n\nBack for its third year\, this event welcomes thou
 sands of families to The Distillery Historic District over the holiday we
 ekend.\n\nApril 3 - 5\, 2026\n\nFree to attend!\n\n\n🐰🐰🐰🐰🐰🐰\n\n\n\n
 10:30am: Registration Opens\n\nHead over to our registration cabins locat
 ed on Gristmill Lane (a short bunny hop away from the Peace Sculpture!). 
 Participants must register before beginning their adventure.\n\nYou can r
 egister at any time between 10:30am - 11:45am. The EGGSTRAVAGANZA portion
  of the event runs for 1 hour from 11am - 12pm. See below for more detail
 s.\n\nRegistration Includes:\n\n1. Access to the EGGSTRAVAGANZA!\n\n2. A 
 complimentary Easter basket may be borrowed\, while supplies last. Partic
 ipants are also encouraged to bring their own basket.\n\n3. A complimenta
 ry chocolate treat bag upon completion of your EGGSTRAVAGANZA!\n\n\n🐰🐰?
 ?🐰🐰🐰\n\n\n\n11am - 12pm: The EGGSTRAVAGANZA\n\nEaster just got eggstra
  exciting this year with over 20\,000 colourful eggs to be collected thro
 ughout The Distillery Historic District!\n\nTWO WAYS TO EXPERIENCE THE EG
 GSTRAVAGANZA:\n\n1. Hunt Across the Site at Your Own Pace\n\nStroll our c
 obblestone streets and collect as many eggs as you can fit into your bask
 et. No eggs in sight? Do not fret! Our eggceptional team is constantly re
 plenishing eggs throughout the site.\n\nOpen from 11am - 12pm.\n\n2. Visi
 t The Little Bunny Patio\n\nIf you have a little bunny in your family and
  are looking for a more relaxed egg hunt and activities\, visit our Littl
 e Bunny Patio on Trinity Street. Recommended for ages 4 and under.\n\nOpe
 ns at 11am. Stay and play until 1pm.\n\n\nFinish with a sweet reward!\n\n
 All participants leave with a delicious chocolate treat bag! When your ba
 sket is full\, return your colourful eggs to the cabins on Gristmill Lane
  to redeem your chocolate. Please return your colourful eggs and borrowed
  baskets before hopping home to ensure everybunny has a chance to play.\n
 \n\n🐰🐰🐰🐰🐰🐰\n\n\n\n12:15pm: Raffle\n\nJoin us for our Easter raffle 
 at the registration cabins on Gristmill Lane at 12:15pm.\n\nThis is an in
 -person raffle. You must be present to win! Tickets will be distributed t
 o those in attendance beginning at 12pm.\n\nPRIZES INCLUDE:\n\n🐰 Giant 1
 0 lb Chocolate Bunny\n🍫 Chocolate Bunnies & Chocolate Footballs\n🎁 Give
 aways from local Distillery District businesses.\n\n\n🐰🐰🐰🐰🐰🐰\n\n\n\
 nEntertainment & Activities:\n\n\n🐰\n\nPlay the EGG SCRAMBLE!\n\nOpen fr
 om 11am - 12pm.\n\nLineup on the north end of Trinity Street to play the 
 EGG SCRAMBLE!\n\nPlayers have 60 seconds to get cracking and hunt through
  thousands of eggs. Scramble\, shake\, and race the clock - how many eggs
  can you rattle before time runs out?! If you hear a bell inside an egg\,
  you win a prize!\n\n\n🐰\n\nMeet the Easter Bunny!\n\n11am - 12pm inside
  of the Little Bunny Patio (ages 4 and under).\n\n12pm - 1pm on Trinity S
 treet.\n\n\n🐰\n\nGames & Colouring Tables – free to play!\n\nAvailable f
 rom 10:30am - 1pm\n\n\n🐰\n\nVisit Alley Press photos on Trinity Street.\
 n\nPay-what-you-can photo keepsakes.\n\n\n\n🐰🐰🐰🐰🐰🐰\n\n\n\nWe hope t
 o see you there!\n\nQuestions about our event? Our team is here to help. 
 Contact us! events@thedistillerydistrict.com mailto:events@thedistilleryd
 istrict.com\n\nNote:\n\nThis is an outdoor event that will run rain or sh
 ine. In the event of severe or inclement weather\, updates will be commun
 icated on this page\, and via our social media. Follow us for real-time u
 pdates!: @distilleryto\n\nWhile all are welcome\, this event is best enjo
 yed by families with children aged 12 and under.
CATEGORIES:
