SUMMARY: Curtain Up: In Creation Lab
DESCRIPTION:Inspired by Christina Anderson’s How to Catch Creation\, Curt
 ain Up: In Creation Lab is a six week drop-in program for youth in grades
  10-12 who want to explore storytelling through theatre\, spoken word\, p
 erformance\, and collective collage.\n\nTogether\, participants will expe
 riment with creative expression\, share ideas and bring their stories to 
 life in a collaborative and community-driven space.\n\nThe first 5 partic
 ipants to sign up for March 24 will get one free ticket for Detroit: Musi
 c of the Motor City https://www.soulpepper.ca/performances/detroit .\n\nT
 he first 5 participants to sign up for April 28 will get one free ticket 
 for How to Catch Creation https://www.soulpepper.ca/performances/howtocat
 chcreation .\n\nParticipate how you choose! Registration is open for the 
 following dates:\n\nMarch 24\nMarch 31\nApril 7\nApril 14\nApril 21\nApri
 l 28\n\nPlease register at the following link: https://tickets.youngcentr
 e.ca/15985 https://tickets.youngcentre.ca/15985 .\n\nFor questions email:
  maricris.rivera@soulpepper.ca mailto:maricris.rivera@soulpepper.ca
CATEGORIES:free,youth,high-school,storytelling
